The Biden-Harris Administration is taking new actions to advance equality, inclusion, and opportunity for transgender Americans. They are hosting a White House Virtual Convening on Transgender Equality, featuring transgender youth advocates, leaders, and officials from the administration. The administration is also creating a new Interagency Working Group on Safety, Inclusion, and Opportunity for Transgender Americans to coordinate policies across various departments. Steps are being taken to expand the availability of accurate Federal IDs for transgender individuals, and the Federal government is aiming to become a model employer for transgender public servants. The Department of Veterans Affairs is removing outdated restrictions to allow transgender veterans to access comprehensive gender-affirming care. Additionally, a toolkit on equality and inclusion for transgender Americans has been released. These actions build on previous efforts by the administration to advance equality for transgender individuals.